subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
First two gastral segments completely ferruginous, and in some specimens this coloration covering up to basal half of third segment (
Figs 42
& 
51
). Dense silvery setae on clypeus, frons, pronotum, apex and sides of scutum, scutellum, metanotum and propodeum, having a yellow tint in some parts (
Figs 43–45, 48, 49, 51–55
). Silvery pile band on apex of Gt1–Gt3, Gt4 without pile band, Gt5 extensively covered with short silvery setae (
Figs 46 & 51
). FEMALE. BL. 
9.05–9.25 mm
. Anterior clypeal teeth as in figures 44 & 63. Propodeal dorsum rugoso-reticulate (
Fig. 48
). Pygidium triangular, with lateral carinae as in figure 50. MALE. BL. 
7.82–7.95 mm
. Anterior clypeal margin as in figures 43 & 64. F1 2.0–2.5 × its apical width (
Fig. 54
). Propodeum rugose (
Fig. 55
).
